column1: [0]:modern software development heavily relies on continuous testing to ensure the reliability and functionality of applications.
[1]:testing strategies range from unit testing and integration testing to system testing and user acceptance testing.
[2]:automated testing, implemented through frameworks such as selenium and junit, enhances efficiency by executing test scripts without human intervention.
[3]:continuous integration and continuous deployment cicd pipelines streamline the development process by incorporating automated testing at various stages.
[4]:regression testing helps detect unintended side effects of code modifications, while performance testing assesses an applications behavior under different loads.
[5]:security testing, on the other hand, identifies vulnerabilities that could be exploited by malicious actors.
[6]:by integrating robust testing methodologies, software teams can enhance product quality and user satisfaction, ensuring seamless deployment in real-world environments.
